reviews.text: Good food, harder to find .. take lift up to top floor but still need to walk up one flight of steps
Great food and great service
Classic and nostalgic... food is really delicious..👍🏻

Taking the elevator from the lobby of the Nathan Hotel does not get you to the Penthouse. Once you get to the 14/F, you have to walk up a flight of stairs.

The service was pathetic. The waiters and waitresses were not rude when they were actually interacting with us. The problem was that they ignored us, while they were busy setting up tables and delivering food to other patrons. We were seated for 15 minutes before we were able to get hold of a menu. The staff was also quite disorganized; often serving the wrong food.

The dim sum, the deep-fried crab claws and the Fujian fried rice were alright, but not good enough to make up for all the aggravation.
A nice restaurant.

reviews.text: Very beautiful hotel! Amazing staff, very helpful. I enjoyed my stay here. Would definitely recommend.

Our room was upgraded for free to a suite. We thought it was in such a good spot we stayed an extra night. Perfect location for the jade and night markets and walking around Kowloon. Everything is nearby we didn't bother using the MTR as everywhere was walkable. There's a supermarket over the road, good prices on wine and beer with a good selection of wine. Avoid 7 11 for wine, poor selection and expensive. Staff were very nice.

Larger than average room sizes, and very well placed. It's walking distance from either jordan station or yau ma tei, with plenty of things to see and do within the vicinity. Several Michelin recommended spots to eat at nearby as well. 

Rooms are amply equipped and service is good. Nice hotel and nice price in an excellent area.
Great place to rest your tired holiday legs, great comfy bed, ultra clean rooms, friendly staff

Excellent hotel! Great rooms with comfy beds.
Very modern with great technology.
Breakfast selection was fantastic.
Overall an awesome place to stay right in the heart of Kowloon.

result.name: 彌敦酒店

reviews.text: 招待幾有禮👏👏
一般細小酒店🏩

在彌敦道上，離佐敦地下鐵只要4分鐘，出口有電梯可以推行李，門面看起來雖然簡單，房間很大，都會強調幫你升級，電視是和室內所有的燈以及冷氣都可以從一台平板中控，非常的方便。最好的是有一台handy上網帶出飯店，還能撥電話訂餐廳，打國際電話也有免費的國家，可惜不含台灣。早餐在15樓，雖然款式不多，但是精緻好吃，燒賣是我們吃過比大部分茶餐廳好吃的；有現煎的太陽蛋還有歐姆蛋，非常好吃，鬆餅機是全自動的，擠一團麵糊到烤熟都是全自動，非常新鮮。
咖啡和紅茶旁邊有鮮奶,品質不錯，還有外帶杯可以讓大家帶走，誠意十足。佳佳甜品就在斜對面，非常方便，興記煲仔飯也在附近，更有非常多換匯的店舖，生活機能太好了。走路就能到逛街的地方，只怕荷包消廋！
地㸃交通方便、房間設備也ok。
